templates.name: ListBox
templates.help:
• Double tap on the shape to change list box
• Each line of the text is a list item
• Selected list item starts with *
• Disabled list item starts with -
• If a list item has to start with * then while editing the list item, start it with \*
• If a list item has to start with - then while editing the list item, start it with \-

• Selected button starts with *
• If a button text has to start with * then while editing the button text, start it with \*

templates.name: Menu

generator.text:
Open,CTRL+O
*Open Recent,>
---
[O]Option One
Option Two
=
[x]Toggle Item
-Disabled Item
Exit,CTRL+Q

templates.help:
• Double tap to edit the menu
• Each line represent a menu item
• If a line is --- or = that means that is a separator line
• Selected menu item starts with *
• Disabled menu item starts with -
• A menu item can optionally starts with these icons: checked ([x]), dot ([O])
• A menu item can have text on right side. The right side text is separated by comma from the left side text. For example Open,CTRL+O mean left side text is Open and right side text is CTRL+O. Comma can be escaped as \, in case the left side text needs to have comma

generator.text:

[-]Delete an item
*Selected item,OK

   Another item with spaces

templates.help:
• Double tap to edit the menu
• Each line represent a menu item
• Selected menu item starts with *
• Disabled menu item starts with -
• If menu text has to start with * or - then it should be escaped as \* or \-
• A menu item can optionally starts with one of these icons: checked ([x]), dot ([O]), add ([+]), remove([-])
• A menu item can optionally ends with one of these icons: on([on]), off([off]), detail indicator([>]), bars([=])
• A menu item can have text on right side. The right side text is separated by comma from the left side text. For example SomeText,OK mean left side text is SomeText and right side text is OK. Comma can be escaped as \, in case the left side text needs to have comma

templates.help:
• Double tap to edit the tree
• Each line represent a tree item
• Selected tree item starts with *
• Disabled tree item starts with -
• A tree item can optionally starts with these icons: [+], [-], [folder], [folder-open], [file], [>] and [v]
• For nested tree item or hierarchical tree item, start the tree item with space (or spaces for multi level nesting)

templates.name: Data Grid
templates.help:
• Double tap on the grid to edit
• Each line of text represent a row
• Each line has one or more grid cells which are separated by comma
• Selected row starts with *
• A cell can be disabled if it starts with -
• A cell can contains icon from one of these: [+], [-], [v], [O], [( )], [ ], [x]
• A cell can be multi line by separating lines by \n
• The last line is for column width. The column with is specified as Number and Align e.g. 12C. The alignments are L: Left, C: center, R: right. The zero width means width to fit the text. Otherwise the width number specifies the ratio. For example if a column has width 15 and other has 55, that means the width ratio of these two columns are 15:55

templates.name: Tab Bar
templates.help:
• Double tap on the tab bar to change the tabs
• Each comma separated text is a tab item
• Selected tab text starts with *
• If a tab text has to start with * then it should be escaped i.e. it should start with \*
• For multi line tab item text use \n to separate lines
